author: Gaurav Dhami

text: ¬†@Gaurav Dhami¬† That is normal when we start. I had the same dilemma. Only thing is try to solve as many problems of different nature as you can and it will help you establish a proper context of what logic to apply for what problem. If you watched Taufiq's video on solving complex queries, he used windows function ROW_NUMBER to create a new column with index values and then subtracted it with id to arrive at a difference. If difference value number was same, that was the row of interest which will solve the problem of finding consecutive rows with less than zero temperature. So now you know that whenever you need to solve a similar problem, you can use this logic. Like that you would keep on building your wealth of solution ideas.
